HEADWORD: Xyletic
<hw>Xy*let"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, a complex acid related to
mesitylenic acid, obtained as a white crystalline substance by the
action of sodium and carbon dioxide on crude xylenol.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Xylic</ent>⟦br⟧
